This paper is about deep learning frameworks and their ability to efficiently execute large computations while also supporting straightforward programming models. The paper specifically focuses on JANUS, a system that converts imperative DL programs written in Python into a symbolic dataflow graph. This topic falls under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), neural networks (cs.NE), and programming languages (cs.PL).
